      "content": "i hear that, but isn't there a massive difference between a \"police force\" and being able to protect your own family in your own home right now? it feels like the \"balancing rights\" argument is just a way to say the second amendment isn't actually a right if the government can just regulate it away. if the laws only affect people who follow them, doesn't that make the laws fundamentally flawed from a practical standpoint?",
